HEADWORD: Charioteer
<hw>Char`i*ot*eer"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who drives a chariot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>A constellation. See
<er>Auriga</er>, and <er>Wagones</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Charism</ent>⟦br⟧
